1
00:00:41,792 --> 00:00:45,963
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:49,675 --> 00:00:52,511
<i>You all remember</i>
<i>the ill-omened star, right?</i>

3
00:00:53,387 --> 00:00:56,223
<i>The comet that arrived</i>
<i>with the solar eclipse three months ago</i>

4
00:00:56,306 --> 00:00:58,976
<i>is still floating in the night sky.</i>

5
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:01,979
<i>I feel like I'd miss it</i>
<i>if it suddenly disappeared.</i>

6
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:07,150
<i>So you should take</i>
<i>a picture of it right now.</i>

7
00:01:07,693 --> 00:01:10,404
<i>Unlike shooting stars or meteors</i>

8
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:12,489
<i>that appear and vanish</i>
<i>in the blink of an eye,</i>

9
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:14,324
<i>this appeared without a sound.</i>

10
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:18,078
<i>And for all we know,</i>

11
00:01:18,579 --> 00:01:21,832
<i>it could leave us without any warning.</i>

12
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:26,086
EPISODE 10
HOPE, DESPAIR, AND LONGING

13
00:01:36,388 --> 00:01:39,474
<i>I'm so sorry,</i>
<i>but the Chairman is sleeping.</i>

14
00:01:39,975 --> 00:01:43,478
Well, I can't really open the door
for you right now.

15
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:47,274
I'll let him know you stopped by
when he wakes up.

16
00:01:47,899 --> 00:01:48,984
Okay.

17
00:02:07,461 --> 00:02:10,380
So I am
the exiled Grand Prince,

18
00:02:10,881 --> 00:02:13,133
and you are that court lady?

19
00:02:13,216 --> 00:02:14,343
That is correct.

20
00:02:15,719 --> 00:02:17,054
So it wasn't some nonsense dream.

21
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:20,891
I was seeing a past life
or something like that?

22
00:02:22,601 --> 00:02:23,685
I guess so.

23
00:02:24,978 --> 00:02:26,229
Then what about you?

24
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,982
Did you time travel or something?

25
00:02:29,775 --> 00:02:31,109
"Time…"

26
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:33,695
No, it is not that.

27
00:02:33,779 --> 00:02:35,030
My soul

28
00:02:35,113 --> 00:02:36,782
transcended time and space.

29
00:02:39,326 --> 00:02:40,744
That's the exact same thing.

30
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:43,830
No wonder your English is so bad.

31
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:46,958
But still, this isn't <i>The X-Files.</i>

32
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:48,418
Does this make any sense?

33
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:50,754
You said you believed me.

34
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:52,589
Well, yeah.

35
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:54,633
I mean, I still can't wrap
my head around it,

36
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:57,803
but I can't deny the situation
unfolding before me.

37
00:02:59,846 --> 00:03:00,889
I'll try to accept it.

38
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:03,809
Still, maybe we should go see a doctor--

39
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:04,851
Doctor?

40
00:03:06,436 --> 00:03:09,189
I mean, just in case we both went
crazy at the exact same time.

41
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:12,150
Maybe getting a full checkup would be…

42
00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:14,194
Maybe not.

43
00:03:20,951 --> 00:03:22,327
So does that mean…

44
00:03:24,329 --> 00:03:26,039
we're done testing the waters?

45
00:03:26,581 --> 00:03:29,000
Do you have to ask?
Are you trying to embarrass me?

46
00:03:29,084 --> 00:03:30,419
I mean, I just thought

47
00:03:30,502 --> 00:03:32,504
I might be getting ahead of myself.

48
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:37,217
After all that lip-smashing?

49
00:03:38,051 --> 00:03:41,263
If I were still testing the waters,
that would be shameless of me.

50
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:46,309
I see.

51
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,563
Then I guess today is the day

52
00:03:49,646 --> 00:03:51,148
we become undeniably official?

53
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:58,071
Just promise me one thing.

54
00:03:58,155 --> 00:03:59,322
From now on, no--

55
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:00,866
No secrets between us.

56
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:03,368
Right, that.

57
00:04:03,452 --> 00:04:05,245
And if by any chance, Choi Mun-do--

58
00:04:05,328 --> 00:04:08,039
If he makes a move,
I shall alert you promptly.

59
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:10,417
Yeah, I'm the super jealous type.

60
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,626
Screw Choi Mun-do.

61
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:14,129
Just don't talk to any guys.
Don't fraternize with any of them.

62
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,422
Don't even meet them.

63
00:04:15,505 --> 00:04:16,757
Hey.

64
00:04:16,840 --> 00:04:18,925
Then how am I supposed to work?

65
00:04:19,009 --> 00:04:20,594
Half the world is men.

66
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:22,387
Do you want me holed up in my room?

67
00:04:22,471 --> 00:04:24,639
No, I'm just saying. That's all.

68
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,893
On that note…

69
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:32,397
why don't we go inside

70
00:04:32,481 --> 00:04:35,025
and finish our conversation?

71
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:41,698
- Damn it.
- Gosh!

72
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:44,075
Who left this here?

73
00:04:44,159 --> 00:04:45,118
Wait.

74
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:46,536
How long have you been there…

75
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,413
I just came to water the plants

76
00:04:48,497 --> 00:04:50,624
and missed my chance to leave.

77
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,668
Please resume what you were doing.

78
00:04:53,752 --> 00:04:55,086
Why so formal, all of a sudden…

79
00:04:55,170 --> 00:04:56,713
I can water them tomorrow.

80
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,298
No staying overnight.

81
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:01,593
Manager Gu, how could you be so vulgar?

82
00:05:02,511 --> 00:05:03,553
I can't?

83
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:07,057
What do you think?

84
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,355
Right.

85
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,942
It must sound a bit scandalous
to a Joseon woman.

86
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:20,987
No. I am no longer a Joseon woman.

87
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:23,073
Holding back my feelings and agonizing?

88
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:24,991
I am done acting like a fool.

89
00:05:25,075 --> 00:05:27,452
I am just going to give
everything I have now.

90
00:05:37,379 --> 00:05:38,463
Give me some more.

91
00:05:42,217 --> 00:05:45,679
<i>Heat it up and take it twice</i>
<i>a day after meals.</i>

92
00:05:45,762 --> 00:05:48,390
How many times do I have to tell her
this is all a scam?

93
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:50,809
<i>Scam or whatever,</i>
<i>save your smart comments.</i>

94
00:05:50,892 --> 00:05:52,143
<i>Make sure you take it.</i>

95
00:05:52,227 --> 00:05:53,186
What the…

96
00:05:54,896 --> 00:05:56,022
Can she read minds now?

97
00:05:56,106 --> 00:05:58,275
<i>Consider it a favor</i>
<i>bestowed from my heart.</i>

98
00:05:58,358 --> 00:05:59,442
<i>That is all.</i>

99
00:06:00,527 --> 00:06:01,778
"Favor"?

100
00:06:06,241 --> 00:06:08,159
Fine. I'll drink it for you.

101
00:06:18,253 --> 00:06:19,629
<i>I finished the whole pouch.</i>

102
00:06:21,965 --> 00:06:23,842
I am going to be beyond generous.

103
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:25,635
Spend my money without holding back

104
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:28,054
and give my heart without holding back.

105
00:06:28,138 --> 00:06:30,015
Just going to give it away?

106
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:31,391
Here.

107
00:06:32,851 --> 00:06:34,019
Just say the word, Granny.

108
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:36,605
Anything you want? Want some new clothes?

109
00:06:36,688 --> 00:06:38,315
Buy yourself some new clothes first.

110
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,066
You're just wasting all that youth.

111
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:41,651
Yeah.

112
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:42,944
It would be a waste.

113
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:45,947
Once time passes, it never comes back.

114
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:48,116
I shall live without regrets now.

115
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:54,122
I am going to really live my life now.

116
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:55,540
Spread kindness around generously.

117
00:06:55,624 --> 00:06:57,459
That is how one should live.

118
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:01,588
Wow!

119
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:04,257
These apples are sweet.

120
00:07:04,341 --> 00:07:06,635
Snow-kissed and all the sweeter for it.

121
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:10,472
My sweet little girl.

122
00:07:15,602 --> 00:07:16,978
HONEY APPLES

123
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:21,399
Yeah, even apples will just rot
if you save them for too long.

124
00:07:21,483 --> 00:07:23,068
Use it or lose it.

125
00:07:24,694 --> 00:07:26,071
Here, take this.

126
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:28,615
A random apple?

127
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,450
They were selling
snow-kissed apples cheap,

128
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:31,701
so I grabbed the lot.

129
00:07:31,785 --> 00:07:34,371
They might be snow-kissed,
but they're very sweet.

130
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:40,210
What the… Maybe they're poisonous?

131
00:07:40,794 --> 00:07:42,087
That's so funny.

132
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:43,171
- Jesus!
- Manager Gu!

133
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:44,965
You startled me.

134
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,009
You helped me get my place,

135
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:49,552
and you receive my packages.

136
00:07:49,636 --> 00:07:51,471
I have been meaning to thank you properly.

137
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:54,516
There is no building manager
like you in this world.

138
00:07:54,599 --> 00:07:56,184
Let our camaraderie be eternal.

139
00:07:58,728 --> 00:07:59,938
I wondered where you went.

140
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:01,940
I guess our Gwang-nam
was busy hanging laundry.

141
00:08:02,023 --> 00:08:03,316
"Our Gwang-nam"?

142
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,026
Here, have a bite of this apple.

143
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:06,069
It is very sweet.

144
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:07,862
I can just eat this? For free?

145
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:10,198
Of course it's free.
How could I charge you for an apple?

146
00:08:10,281 --> 00:08:11,533
Do you take me for a skinflint?

147
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:13,702
Why the sudden generosity?
It doesn't suit you.

148
00:08:13,785 --> 00:08:15,370
Damned if I do, damned if I do not.

149
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,080
Why does it not suit me?

150
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:18,957
As long as I keep my mouth shut,

151
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,292
people say I look like an angel.

152
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,462
- Who said that? Who?
- The fruit stand lady.

153
00:08:24,546 --> 00:08:28,383
Let me guess. She also said
you looked like you had a heart of gold?

154
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:29,759
Just look at all this.

155
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,220
I knew it.
The bottoms are all frozen and busted.

156
00:08:32,303 --> 00:08:33,388
What? Frozen and busted?

157
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:35,432
- What the…
- Look.

158
00:08:36,141 --> 00:08:38,977
Listen, in my hometown,
we wouldn't even pick these.

159
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:41,646
Damn it. I even had
a box of them delivered.

160
00:08:41,730 --> 00:08:43,356
CHA SE-GYE
HONEY APPLES

161
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,524
Mr. Son.

162
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:48,778
Can you think of anyone
who would send apples to Mr. Cha?

163
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:49,904
I can think of a few.

164
00:08:49,988 --> 00:08:51,614
Apple boxes bring to mind…

165
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:55,118
corruption, bribery, and collusion.

166
00:08:55,201 --> 00:08:56,786
No question about it.

167
00:09:00,457 --> 00:09:02,834
- You're going to open it?
- Step back, Ms. Kim.

168
00:09:02,917 --> 00:09:04,085
It could be a bomb.

169
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:07,297
Maybe you should call security first.

170
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,673
Don't worry.

171
00:09:08,757 --> 00:09:11,676
I may not look it,
but I served in the 1st Marine Division.

172
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:15,138
I was the Poison Dart Frog.

173
00:09:18,058 --> 00:09:19,100
Gosh.

174
00:09:20,477 --> 00:09:21,853
Don't touch that.

175
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,521
Step back, sir.

176
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:26,191
I said don't touch it. It's mine.

177
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:41,873
Yes, that's right. Shin Seo-ri.

178
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:45,085
It's the second gift she's given me.

179
00:09:45,168 --> 00:09:46,544
The second?

180
00:09:47,504 --> 00:09:49,464
- What was the first?
- Herbal medicine.

181
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:51,007
She had some made for me yesterday.

182
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:53,426
Apparently…

183
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,930
she favors me or something.

184
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,473
You know,

185
00:09:58,556 --> 00:10:00,642
once you catch feelings,

186
00:10:00,725 --> 00:10:02,811
worry naturally follows.

187
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:07,315
It's not really about catching feelings.
I think she's genuinely worried.

188
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,152
- About what?
- Your health.

189
00:10:11,236 --> 00:10:12,320
More specifically…

190
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:14,489
your stamina?

191
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,699
Yeah, I think she's worried about that.

192
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:25,542
Stamina?

193
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,460
Sir, anyway, about the nurse…

194
00:10:29,963 --> 00:10:31,256
Right, the nurse.

195
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:32,423
What's going on with her?

196
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:35,009
We're keeping her safe for now.
Once things settle down,

197
00:10:35,093 --> 00:10:36,261
she agreed to turn herself in.

198
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:37,470
All right.

199
00:10:38,096 --> 00:10:39,639
Let's try to minimize losses.

200
00:10:40,682 --> 00:10:41,766
As quietly as possible.

201
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:43,935
And on top of that,

202
00:10:44,018 --> 00:10:45,895
we're looking at a leadership change.

203
00:10:47,105 --> 00:10:48,356
Leadership?

204
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:53,403
Chairman, please forgive me.

205
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:55,155
I have only myself to blame.

206
00:10:55,238 --> 00:10:56,531
Forgive you for what?

207
00:10:57,574 --> 00:10:59,325
You make it sound like I punished you.

208
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:01,578
Please give me one more chance.

209
00:11:03,246 --> 00:11:05,790
You know how hard I've worked
for this company.

210
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,168
But tell me, Mun-do,

211
00:11:08,251 --> 00:11:10,295
what kind of salaryman

212
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:13,006
dedicates his whole life
to a company like that?

213
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:14,507
You only give your all

214
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:16,467
when you think it all belongs to you.

215
00:11:16,551 --> 00:11:17,719
Goodness.

216
00:11:18,344 --> 00:11:20,471
I've kept you working for me for too long.

217
00:11:21,139 --> 00:11:23,600
It's time you took a breather.

218
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:26,603
Go to the US, clear your head,

219
00:11:26,686 --> 00:11:28,813
and be a good father to Seo-jun.

220
00:11:28,897 --> 00:11:30,273
Do that and come back.

221
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:37,989
<i>Grandfather is ruthless.</i>

222
00:11:38,072 --> 00:11:41,242
Who knew he'd bleed
Choi Mun-do dry and exile him to the US?

223
00:11:41,326 --> 00:11:42,660
You already knew?

224
00:11:44,329 --> 00:11:47,290
You thought I must be out of the loop
because of my dating venture?

225
00:11:47,373 --> 00:11:49,751
If I missed something this big,
I should resign.

226
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:53,504
The time has come to start preparing, sir.

227
00:11:53,588 --> 00:11:55,298
Since you already know,
I'll speak plainly.

228
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:57,175
The Chairman called in Attorney Choi

229
00:11:57,258 --> 00:11:59,594
and notarized his will a while ago.

230
00:12:00,929 --> 00:12:03,890
Jeez, Grandfather really needs
to get with the times.

231
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:05,600
A backdoor succession in this day and age?

232
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,520
Let's just wait and see for now.

233
00:12:12,941 --> 00:12:15,026
<i>After you wrap up the brand launch,</i>

234
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:16,653
you can return with confidence.

235
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:17,946
You did enough

236
00:12:18,029 --> 00:12:20,198
to walk back in
with your head held high.

237
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,533
Fine, Grandfather.

238
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:25,161
But I have one condition.

239
00:12:25,245 --> 00:12:26,621
What? A condition?

240
00:12:26,704 --> 00:12:29,082
Let me call off the marriage to Mochang.

241
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:30,583
What?

242
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:32,293
I know you're worried.

243
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:34,379
But you've seen it. I'm more than capable.

244
00:12:34,462 --> 00:12:36,214
I'm calling off the engagement.

245
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:38,800
What did I do in a past life
to deserve this?

246
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:41,719
From my son and now my grandson too…

247
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:44,847
Did you tell your grandfather
about the bug?

248
00:12:44,931 --> 00:12:46,307
Why would I? It'd just worry him.

249
00:12:46,391 --> 00:12:48,559
You should still tell him.

250
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,062
Who knows what he might try next time?

251
00:12:51,813 --> 00:12:53,398
I just have a bad feeling about this.

252
00:12:53,481 --> 00:12:54,857
Think how Grandfather must feel

253
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:56,985
after relying on him all these years.

254
00:12:57,068 --> 00:12:59,404
Once he goes to the US,
there's nothing to worry about.

255
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:00,905
So until then,

256
00:13:00,989 --> 00:13:02,907
Grandfather must never find out.

257
00:13:04,826 --> 00:13:06,411
But will Mun-do go quietly?

258
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:11,833
This is where
"the energy of the universe" is?

259
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,334
Just give it a chance.

260
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:14,544
It may not look like much,

261
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,879
but this place is well-known
among those in the know.

262
00:13:17,839 --> 00:13:21,467
Gosh. How about some refreshments first?

263
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:23,177
I can brew you

264
00:13:23,261 --> 00:13:25,221
this fine instant coffee in a flash.

265
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:27,557
Please just give me a second.

266
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,892
- Sure.
- Pardon me.

267
00:13:30,810 --> 00:13:32,061
Jeez!

268
00:13:32,145 --> 00:13:34,564
I'm the moron for listening
and following you here.

269
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:36,149
Are you ever going to wise up?

270
00:13:36,232 --> 00:13:38,192
Ju-mi, think about it.

271
00:13:38,276 --> 00:13:40,236
Does Father even listen to a word we say?

272
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:42,780
Or does that bastard Cha Se-gye
even give us the time of day?

273
00:13:42,864 --> 00:13:45,533
Mun-do is about to be dead in the water.

274
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:47,952
We don't have any real power anyway.

275
00:13:48,036 --> 00:13:50,705
So you just need to surrender entirely

276
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:52,248
to the energy of the universe.

277
00:13:52,332 --> 00:13:54,125
I mean, sure.

278
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:57,045
But why would you entrust that
to a place like this?

279
00:13:57,128 --> 00:14:00,089
"A place like this"?
Should we just sit on our hands instead?

280
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,883
You need to listen to me.

281
00:14:01,966 --> 00:14:03,968
The lifeline we must snatch
exists elsewhere.

282
00:14:04,052 --> 00:14:06,554
We are currently
at the heart of enemy territory.

283
00:14:07,722 --> 00:14:08,973
Cha Se-gye's…

284
00:14:09,057 --> 00:14:11,184
The gateway to power.

285
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,393
Gateway?

286
00:14:12,477 --> 00:14:13,770
What a shame.

287
00:14:13,853 --> 00:14:17,231
There was never any gateway here
to begin with. Too bad.

288
00:14:17,315 --> 00:14:19,067
You dare try to spy on me?

289
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:22,236
- Begone, evil spirits! Begone!
- Goodness!

290
00:14:22,320 --> 00:14:23,613
- Begone!
- My goodness!

291
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:26,115
- The ancestral spirits are angry!
- Oh my God.

292
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:29,118
- I can't believe this.
- The ancestral spirits are furious!

293
00:14:29,202 --> 00:14:30,953
- They are furious!
- Oh my goodness.

294
00:14:31,579 --> 00:14:32,830
How dare you…

295
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,333
Away with you, you wretches!

296
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,502
Begone, you vile creatures!

297
00:14:37,585 --> 00:14:39,003
Begone this instant!

298
00:14:39,087 --> 00:14:39,962
You hear me?

299
00:14:41,297 --> 00:14:43,549
Why the hell would you buy rotten apples?

300
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,219
They had the gall
to accept money for this?

301
00:14:46,302 --> 00:14:48,429
If I ever see them again,
I shall pulverize them.

302
00:14:48,513 --> 00:14:51,224
But did you really call me here
to do manual labor?

303
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:52,850
Keep business and personal life separate.

304
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:54,477
Gwang-nam, have you no conscience?

305
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,938
You drew triple wages upfront,
and now you don't want to work?

306
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:59,399
Unreal. Earlier, you were all,
"Our Gwang-nam."

307
00:14:59,482 --> 00:15:01,859
How can someone be so hot and cold?

308
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:04,112
Why? Did Mr. Cha suddenly say
he likes nice girls?

309
00:15:04,195 --> 00:15:05,696
No, not exactly…

310
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:08,741
Say what now?

311
00:15:09,409 --> 00:15:10,952
Do not tell me…

312
00:15:11,035 --> 00:15:13,037
His supercar has been here
every other day.

313
00:15:13,121 --> 00:15:14,914
Could you have made it any more obvious?

314
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:16,374
He practically lives here.

315
00:15:16,457 --> 00:15:17,542
You sly fox.

316
00:15:18,543 --> 00:15:20,545
You knew everything and played dumb.

317
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:25,341
Your Highness, it's me. The fortuneteller.

318
00:15:33,474 --> 00:15:35,351
APPOINTMENT NOTICE
CHOI MUN-DO, US BRANCH MANAGER

319
00:15:35,435 --> 00:15:38,312
<i>It's time you took a breather.</i>

320
00:15:38,396 --> 00:15:39,564
<i>Go to the US,</i>

321
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:43,192
and be a good father to Seo-jun.
Do that and come back.

322
00:15:56,247 --> 00:15:57,165
Hey, Seo-jun.

323
00:15:57,248 --> 00:16:00,293
<i>Sir, Seo-jun got into a little accident.</i>

324
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:01,294
An accident?

325
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:03,171
What kind of accident?

326
00:16:03,254 --> 00:16:05,423
<i>He fell during a match earlier,</i>

327
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,008
<i>and we rushed him to the ER.</i>

328
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:09,343
<i>- He tore a ligament.</i>
- And you're just telling me now?

329
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:12,305
<i>Seo-jun begged me not to tell his dad.</i>

330
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:15,558
<i>So I waited until he fell asleep</i>
<i>to call you.</i>

331
00:16:15,641 --> 00:16:16,851
<i>My apologies, sir.</i>

332
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:17,977
Right.

333
00:16:18,603 --> 00:16:20,688
I'm your boss. Not Seo-jun.

334
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:22,815
Don't bother coming in tomorrow.

335
00:16:22,899 --> 00:16:24,734
Your replacement
will arrive before midnight.

336
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,527
Complete the handover and pack up.

337
00:16:49,133 --> 00:16:50,927
<i>But will Mun-do go quietly?</i>

338
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:53,054
Who knows what he might try next time?

339
00:16:53,638 --> 00:16:55,640
Shouldn't we keep an eye
on President Choi Mun-do?

340
00:16:55,723 --> 00:16:58,059
I'm worried about your safety.

341
00:16:59,769 --> 00:17:01,395
He wouldn't try to kill me.

342
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:15,201
HANBIT MENTAL HEALTH CLINIC

343
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:21,999
- What are you doing here?
- Gosh!

344
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:25,002
You should not sneak up
on people like that!

345
00:17:25,086 --> 00:17:26,379
You scared me to death.

346
00:17:26,462 --> 00:17:28,548
Seriously? You're the one
who showed up out of nowhere.

347
00:17:28,631 --> 00:17:29,549
How'd you end up here?

348
00:17:29,632 --> 00:17:32,134
- Mr. Son…
- No, why are you here?

349
00:17:33,177 --> 00:17:34,345
Did something happen?

350
00:17:35,096 --> 00:17:36,097
No.

351
00:17:36,639 --> 00:17:38,349
I wanted to do something with you.

352
00:17:39,308 --> 00:17:40,351
What?

353
00:17:40,434 --> 00:17:41,394
A date.

354
00:17:41,477 --> 00:17:43,479
Let us go on a date, Cha Se-gye.

355
00:17:44,897 --> 00:17:46,065
A date?

356
00:17:47,608 --> 00:17:48,859
All of a sudden?

357
00:17:53,447 --> 00:17:54,323
Let's go.

358
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:01,622
You call this a date?

359
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:03,708
A pilgrimage for pastries?

360
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:05,418
I heard the "ring pastry" here is good.

361
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:08,087
Just look at this mob.
How did they all find out?

362
00:18:16,012 --> 00:18:18,347
I'm the idiot
for expecting something from you.

363
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:20,474
A man of my stature?

364
00:18:20,558 --> 00:18:22,685
Wasting time on the street
just to eat a damn pastry?

365
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:23,936
You think that makes sense?

366
00:18:24,020 --> 00:18:26,230
It is not a waste. It is romance.

367
00:18:26,314 --> 00:18:27,607
I read online

368
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:30,026
that a date is about spending
quality time with your beloved.

369
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:33,029
Eating good food and having fun
is enough for me.

370
00:18:35,031 --> 00:18:37,825
Your beloved? You can do that anytime.

371
00:18:37,908 --> 00:18:40,536
But for a real date,
there should at least be some fireworks.

372
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:42,955
A yacht party with a drone show, at least.

373
00:18:43,998 --> 00:18:45,207
Who wants plain old ordinary?

374
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:47,251
I like it. The plain old ordinary.

375
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:50,254
It is ordinary and nothing special.

376
00:18:50,338 --> 00:18:51,714
That is its charm.

377
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:55,092
As long as I am with you,
it will be special to me.

378
00:18:59,347 --> 00:19:02,099
Well, look at you being so forward.

379
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:06,312
Doing what I like with the person I like

380
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:08,773
has been a lifelong dream.

381
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:09,732
Is that so wrong?

382
00:19:12,193 --> 00:19:13,444
I mean…

383
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:17,573
It's fine, I guess.

384
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:22,828
Then what?

385
00:19:24,205 --> 00:19:26,540
What's next
on your plain old ordinary list?

386
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:45,142
Namsan?

387
00:19:45,226 --> 00:19:46,435
Don't tell me, the cable car?

388
00:19:46,519 --> 00:19:49,230
Shin Seo-ri, is this really
what you want to do?

389
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:51,357
Yeah. Is there a problem?

390
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:52,525
No, it's not that.

391
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:56,028
We should ride that
and go up Namsan too.

392
00:19:56,696 --> 00:19:57,655
I looked it up.

393
00:19:57,738 --> 00:20:00,074
Namsan has long been
a dating landmark for lovers.

394
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:01,575
Landmark?

395
00:20:01,659 --> 00:20:03,577
In Episode 16 of <i>My Lovely Sam Soon,</i>

396
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:05,329
Jin-heon and Sam-soon
smashed their lips here,

397
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:07,206
which is how
the Sam-soon Stairs came to be.

398
00:20:07,289 --> 00:20:08,499
And that is not all.

399
00:20:08,582 --> 00:20:09,959
In Episode 4 of <i>Boys Over Flowers,</i>

400
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:13,045
Namsan is where Geum Jan-di ran
to Gu Jun-pyo and let him in.

401
00:20:13,129 --> 00:20:14,422
Those are all so old.

402
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:16,132
Of course, it is not just for lovers.

403
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:18,259
In Episode 122 of
<i>High Kick Through the Roof,</i>

404
00:20:18,342 --> 00:20:21,095
Se-kyung stubbornly insisted
that Shin-ae was 47 months old,

405
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:22,555
so she could ride for free.

406
00:20:22,638 --> 00:20:24,390
It touched the hearts of an entire nation.

407
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:25,391
- And also--
- Stop.

408
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:27,226
Okay, fine.

409
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:28,394
I came fully prepared today,

410
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:30,271
so you just need to follow my lead.

411
00:20:45,619 --> 00:20:47,538
- Hello.
- Hello.

412
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:57,298
Cha Se-gye, look at that.

413
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:10,686
We are moving!

414
00:21:18,986 --> 00:21:20,362
Be careful, Shin Seo-ri.

415
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:22,740
One wrong move, and we could fall.

416
00:21:22,823 --> 00:21:24,241
Fall?

417
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:30,998
Wait.

418
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:35,419
<i>Hold on.</i>
<i>We are hanging on by a thread here.</i>

419
00:21:35,503 --> 00:21:36,796
I am just going to walk up.

420
00:21:36,879 --> 00:21:38,547
Let us ask them to open the door.

421
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:41,926
Hear me! Open this door!

422
00:21:42,009 --> 00:21:43,844
- Hey! Open the door!
- Hey, Shin Seo-ri. Hold on.

423
00:21:43,928 --> 00:21:46,013
- Hey!
- You're embarrassing me. Stay still.

424
00:21:46,096 --> 00:21:47,681
Who cares about being embarrassed?

425
00:21:47,765 --> 00:21:48,974
We need to survive first.

426
00:21:49,058 --> 00:21:50,476
Hear me! Hey!

427
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:52,520
- Hey.
- Let go of me!

428
00:21:53,103 --> 00:21:55,481
We won't fall. I can't even make a joke?

429
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:57,316
A joke?

430
00:21:57,399 --> 00:21:58,943
You joke about human lives?

431
00:21:59,527 --> 00:22:00,653
Drop dead, Cha Se-gye.

432
00:22:04,782 --> 00:22:06,200
- Are you insane?
- Yeah, I am!

433
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:07,535
- What are they doing?
- Seriously?

434
00:22:07,618 --> 00:22:08,953
- What a nuisance.
- Unreal.

435
00:22:09,036 --> 00:22:11,664
- What's wrong with them?
- Lovers' quarrel?

436
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:23,592
Cha Se-gye, look at that.

437
00:22:29,348 --> 00:22:32,101
I'm here. Where are you?

438
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:34,103
<i>Sorry, I had a bathroom emergency.</i>

439
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:36,856
<i>Can you just park our van for me?</i>

440
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:38,107
What?

441
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:40,734
I'm not a valet. Why would I park the van?

442
00:22:40,818 --> 00:22:42,486
<i>Stop whining and park it.</i>

443
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:44,113
Excuse me? Listen. Hello--

444
00:22:46,615 --> 00:22:47,783
Damn it.

445
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:49,368
I can't believe this.

446
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:55,082
Screw this full-time job business.

447
00:22:55,165 --> 00:22:57,543
I'm quitting as soon
as that paycheck hits.

448
00:22:57,626 --> 00:22:59,587
Screw that triple pay or whatever.

449
00:23:18,731 --> 00:23:19,690
No.

450
00:23:20,816 --> 00:23:22,776
Damn it. Why haven't you been picking up?

451
00:23:22,860 --> 00:23:24,528
I've been waiting forever.

452
00:23:25,237 --> 00:23:27,406
Wait. Hold on.

453
00:23:27,489 --> 00:23:30,284
Save the excuses and go straight
to Geumson Jongga.

454
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:33,078
And don't forget to order
the spicy chicken feet like last time.

455
00:23:33,162 --> 00:23:34,663
Geumson Jongga--

456
00:23:34,747 --> 00:23:37,207
I'm tired, so don't talk to me
until we arrive.

457
00:23:38,542 --> 00:23:40,753
What are you doing? Drive. Let's go.

458
00:23:49,136 --> 00:23:51,096
Cha Se-gye, look at all this.

459
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:53,766
Look at this unobstructed view.
I see why this is a landmark.

460
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:56,727
And in terms of feng shui,
there is no finer spot than this.

461
00:23:57,227 --> 00:24:00,606
Only you would come all this way
and start going on about feng shui.

462
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:03,025
Hold on. That is…

463
00:24:22,461 --> 00:24:25,381
Cha Se-gye,
I know what this is. Love padlocks.

464
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:28,592
Left by lovers as tokens
of their eternal vow.

465
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,680
Maybe we should do one too?

466
00:24:36,392 --> 00:24:37,476
No.

467
00:24:39,103 --> 00:24:40,145
Why not?

468
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:42,481
Let's do one.

469
00:24:42,564 --> 00:24:45,317
It's a bit childish,
but we came all this way.

470
00:24:45,401 --> 00:24:47,111
Let's just promise eternity.

471
00:24:47,194 --> 00:24:48,779
Forget it.

472
00:24:48,862 --> 00:24:51,782
I hear it is forever in name
but not in practice.

473
00:24:51,865 --> 00:24:54,827
If our lock is gone
the next time we come here,

474
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:56,578
I think I would be sad.

475
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:00,082
So that is why I do not want to.

476
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,711
Why overthink it like that?
It's just for fun.

477
00:25:03,794 --> 00:25:05,796
I hear they have a far-seeing glass here.

478
00:25:05,879 --> 00:25:07,131
Where could they be?

479
00:25:08,257 --> 00:25:09,341
Wait for me.

480
00:25:15,806 --> 00:25:18,767
Be still, my heart.
Please just shut up already.

481
00:25:20,394 --> 00:25:21,603
Damn dickheads.

482
00:25:21,687 --> 00:25:23,188
Such pieces of shit.

483
00:25:23,272 --> 00:25:24,565
These sons of bitches.

484
00:25:24,648 --> 00:25:25,524
You fucking bastards!

485
00:25:25,607 --> 00:25:27,901
They must be completely insane.

486
00:25:27,985 --> 00:25:29,987
One minute, I'm their type for life,

487
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:32,406
saying I bring honor
to the country with my face.

488
00:25:32,489 --> 00:25:34,283
And now, they say I have dead fish eyes?

489
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:35,576
That I'm stuck in a rut?

490
00:25:35,659 --> 00:25:37,161
Nitpicking left and right!

491
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:39,580
Those fish-eyed bastards!
How dare they!

492
00:25:39,663 --> 00:25:42,374
Just look at the comments.
They say my acting sucks.

493
00:25:42,458 --> 00:25:43,834
As if bad acting is any easier?

494
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:45,878
It takes a shit load of work too!

495
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:47,337
What do they know about acting?

496
00:25:47,421 --> 00:25:50,340
How dare they call it bad acting?
Fucking bastards.

497
00:25:50,424 --> 00:25:52,384
Right? They're total fucking bastards.

498
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:55,095
But did you catch a cold
or something? You sound…

499
00:25:57,181 --> 00:25:58,766
Who are you?

500
00:25:58,849 --> 00:26:00,893
Hello, Ji-hyo. I'm Shin Seo--

501
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:04,021
Shin Seo-ri's Mr. Supercar?
What are you doing here?

502
00:26:04,104 --> 00:26:06,190
- What?
- Watch out!

503
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:07,483
Watch out!

504
00:26:09,443 --> 00:26:10,527
So,

505
00:26:11,195 --> 00:26:13,447
you're not her Mr. Supercar?
You're her manager?

506
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:17,159
Not dressed vintage, just shabby.

507
00:26:18,494 --> 00:26:21,121
Why were you driving my van?
You should have said something.

508
00:26:21,205 --> 00:26:23,165
I tried to tell you,

509
00:26:23,248 --> 00:26:25,292
but you told me not to talk to you.

510
00:26:25,375 --> 00:26:27,211
I can't believe this.

511
00:26:27,294 --> 00:26:30,380
Everything goes to hell
whenever Shin Seo-ri's involved.

512
00:26:30,464 --> 00:26:33,342
Anyway, you're here now.
I'm going to head out.

513
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:35,803
I can't believe this.

514
00:26:35,886 --> 00:26:36,845
Hold on a second.

515
00:26:36,929 --> 00:26:39,014
Yes, Ji-hyo? Can I get you something?

516
00:26:39,098 --> 00:26:40,182
No hate comments, right?

517
00:26:42,059 --> 00:26:43,227
Hate comments?

518
00:26:43,894 --> 00:26:47,147
You know, I've been
in this industry for 20 years now.

519
00:26:47,231 --> 00:26:49,566
So many fawn over you,

520
00:26:49,650 --> 00:26:51,735
then curse you out behind your back.

521
00:26:51,819 --> 00:26:54,905
I've come across so many
of those grinning dickheads, you see.

522
00:26:56,990 --> 00:26:58,534
Let's be careful with our words.

523
00:26:59,785 --> 00:27:01,286
Okay?

524
00:27:01,370 --> 00:27:02,287
Yes.

525
00:27:04,498 --> 00:27:05,457
Shit!

526
00:27:08,502 --> 00:27:09,920
Grinning pricks.

527
00:27:11,922 --> 00:27:14,550
Cha Se-gye, from my window,

528
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:17,177
Namsan Tower is the size of a nail.

529
00:27:17,803 --> 00:27:19,763
So I never imagined it would be this big.

530
00:27:19,847 --> 00:27:21,306
I am so glad we came.

531
00:27:23,350 --> 00:27:25,519
Makes sense if it looked that small.

532
00:27:25,602 --> 00:27:27,771
From my place, it's the size of an arm.

533
00:27:27,855 --> 00:27:29,857
An arm? You can see it that well?

534
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:33,306
Cha Se-gye, you have
really made it in this world.

535
00:27:34,361 --> 00:27:36,655
Does seeing Namsan mean I made it?

536
00:27:36,738 --> 00:27:38,615
Of course it does.

537
00:27:38,699 --> 00:27:41,118
I hear the measure of success here
is whether you can see

538
00:27:41,201 --> 00:27:42,494
Namsan Tower or not.

539
00:27:42,578 --> 00:27:44,204
Arm-sized? You hit the jackpot.

540
00:27:45,497 --> 00:27:46,707
Then next time,

541
00:27:47,332 --> 00:27:49,918
want to see
the arm-sized Namsan Tower at my place?

542
00:27:53,547 --> 00:27:54,590
It's even better at night.

543
00:27:55,424 --> 00:27:58,552
You know, you are always trying
to lure people into your house.

544
00:27:58,635 --> 00:28:00,470
You tried to sneak
into my place yesterday.

545
00:28:00,554 --> 00:28:01,889
Now you want me to go to yours?

546
00:28:01,972 --> 00:28:03,265
What do you take me for?

547
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:05,559
I was innocently offering you
a tour of my place.

548
00:28:05,642 --> 00:28:07,686
Why must that tour happen at night?

549
00:28:12,900 --> 00:28:14,693
Fine, it's because I'm lonely.

550
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:17,404
- Lonely?
- Of course I'm lonely.

551
00:28:19,281 --> 00:28:21,283
Even I get lonely sometimes.

552
00:28:24,870 --> 00:28:27,539
<i>Mr. Cha must feel so lonely.</i>

553
00:28:27,623 --> 00:28:29,875
That's no way for a family to behave.

554
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,044
Earlier, his aunts?

555
00:28:32,127 --> 00:28:34,588
Some relatives of his came to see me.

556
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:38,175
It seemed like they came to see
what they could find out about you two.

557
00:28:38,258 --> 00:28:41,845
They were talking
about some "doorknob of power."

558
00:28:41,929 --> 00:28:47,017
I'm asking you to stick by
that punk Se-gye like super taffy.

559
00:28:48,143 --> 00:28:49,561
"Poverty amidst plenty."

560
00:28:49,645 --> 00:28:51,563
"Relative deprivation."

561
00:28:52,773 --> 00:28:54,233
Something like that.

562
00:28:55,776 --> 00:28:58,195
<i>This man is opening his heart to me.</i>

563
00:28:58,278 --> 00:28:59,821
<i>Probably only to me.</i>

564
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:01,240
Do not worry.

565
00:29:01,907 --> 00:29:03,450
I will not let you be lonely.

566
00:29:03,533 --> 00:29:05,535
What? What was that?

567
00:29:06,411 --> 00:29:08,997
I will make sure you are not alone.

568
00:29:10,832 --> 00:29:12,459
You can trust me.

569
00:29:28,809 --> 00:29:31,395
<i>I will make sure you are not alone.</i>

570
00:29:31,979 --> 00:29:33,146
<i>You can trust me.</i>

571
00:29:35,023 --> 00:29:36,692
Don't forget that promise, Shin Seo-ri.

572
00:29:38,402 --> 00:29:39,695
There is

573
00:29:39,778 --> 00:29:41,321
no turning back for you now.

574
00:29:54,459 --> 00:29:56,753
- Here.
- Thank you so much.

575
00:29:57,504 --> 00:29:59,339
- Here you go.
- Thanks. Appreciate it.

576
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:01,550
Shin Seo-ri.

577
00:30:01,633 --> 00:30:03,510
- What?
- Are you in a good mood again?

578
00:30:03,593 --> 00:30:04,928
Why are you so happy?

579
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:06,596
Perfect timing. Here.

580
00:30:07,306 --> 00:30:08,348
Is this for me?

581
00:30:08,432 --> 00:30:09,433
What is it?

582
00:30:09,516 --> 00:30:11,935
It's candied apple.
I made it myself last night.

583
00:30:12,019 --> 00:30:13,312
Look at you handing out presents.

584
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:15,480
Looks like life's been
pretty sweet for you lately.

585
00:30:15,564 --> 00:30:16,648
Enjoy it.

586
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:18,859
You there!

587
00:30:18,942 --> 00:30:20,068
Where is the chief?

588
00:30:20,152 --> 00:30:22,404
The director is on his way.
Why do you ask?

589
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,072
Share this with everyone. Here.

590
00:30:24,156 --> 00:30:25,490
Do not keep it all to yourself.

591
00:30:25,574 --> 00:30:27,075
Take your costume first.

592
00:30:30,162 --> 00:30:31,079
What's this?

593
00:30:31,163 --> 00:30:32,622
A bribe? Jeez.

594
00:30:36,376 --> 00:30:37,669
- Here.
- Thank you.

595
00:30:37,753 --> 00:30:41,048
Even when Shin Seo-ri gives bribes,
they have to be so undeniably her.

596
00:30:41,131 --> 00:30:42,090
What's with this <i>yakgwa?</i>

597
00:30:42,174 --> 00:30:44,134
It's <i>jeonggwa,</i> not <i>yakgwa.</i>

598
00:30:44,217 --> 00:30:46,678
We can't eat this.
Who knows what's in it?

599
00:30:52,768 --> 00:30:55,103
Damn dickheads. Such pieces of shit.

600
00:30:55,187 --> 00:30:57,522
These sons of bitches.
You fucking bastards!

601
00:30:57,606 --> 00:31:00,067
They must be completely insane.

602
00:31:01,943 --> 00:31:04,112
What if he posts something weird online?

603
00:31:05,322 --> 00:31:07,574
I should've put the fear of God in him.

604
00:31:14,539 --> 00:31:16,833
Hey, Shin Seo-ri. About your manager…

605
00:31:16,917 --> 00:31:18,210
I don't like him. Fire him.

606
00:31:18,293 --> 00:31:19,961
What sort of hogwash is that?

607
00:31:20,504 --> 00:31:21,713
When did you two meet?

608
00:31:23,256 --> 00:31:24,257
You know…

609
00:31:24,841 --> 00:31:27,719
I've seen him in passing,
and he has a face you just can't trust.

610
00:31:27,803 --> 00:31:29,096
Don't argue with me.

611
00:31:29,179 --> 00:31:31,139
I'll recommend you
someone more suitable, so replace him.

612
00:31:31,223 --> 00:31:32,432
Worry about your own face.

613
00:31:32,516 --> 00:31:33,725
Wretched minx.

614
00:31:34,559 --> 00:31:35,644
Why, you little…

615
00:31:36,728 --> 00:31:39,606
We still have a long way to go
before Songjin Resort construction begins.

616
00:31:39,689 --> 00:31:41,400
What's with this sudden transfer
to the US?

617
00:31:41,483 --> 00:31:43,276
The vendors are complaining too.

618
00:31:43,360 --> 00:31:45,529
They all signed on
because of President Choi Mun-do.

619
00:31:45,612 --> 00:31:47,823
So they're worried
about unnecessary roadblocks.

620
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:51,451
I just don't understand what led
the Chairman to make such a decision.

621
00:31:53,662 --> 00:31:56,581
Don't tell me he plans
to put <i>him</i> in the empty seat.

622
00:31:58,625 --> 00:31:59,751
<i>You all remember, right?</i>

623
00:31:59,835 --> 00:32:01,420
<i>His so-called restructuring</i>

624
00:32:01,503 --> 00:32:04,381
<i>toppled CEOs like dominoes.</i>

625
00:32:04,464 --> 00:32:06,425
<i>It was quite a lengthy bloodbath.</i>

626
00:32:06,508 --> 00:32:07,676
<i>How could we forget?</i>

627
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:10,137
<i>Even if he's the Chairman's direct heir,</i>
<i>that kind of man</i>

628
00:32:10,220 --> 00:32:13,348
<i>must never be allowed to set foot</i>
<i>in the Chail Group lobby.</i>

629
00:32:16,518 --> 00:32:17,519
<i>But why did you suddenly</i>

630
00:32:17,602 --> 00:32:18,770
<i>change your mind?</i>

631
00:32:18,854 --> 00:32:20,021
<i>You said you'd wait and see.</i>

632
00:32:20,105 --> 00:32:22,524
<i>They say the best defense is</i>
<i>a good offense, don't they?</i>

633
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:24,568
<i>And the best offense is striking first.</i>

634
00:32:25,652 --> 00:32:26,736
Unbelievable.

635
00:32:30,907 --> 00:32:32,826
Is someone talking about me?
My ears are burning.

636
00:32:32,909 --> 00:32:35,120
Sir, how does it feel to be back?

637
00:32:38,582 --> 00:32:39,749
The air is really stale.

638
00:32:41,543 --> 00:32:43,420
Let's change the air purifiers first.

639
00:32:44,671 --> 00:32:46,673
Let's all calm down for now.

640
00:32:48,091 --> 00:32:49,468
I'm still here.

641
00:32:51,344 --> 00:32:53,346
I won't step down that easily.

642
00:32:59,853 --> 00:33:02,439
Mr. Choi, Mr. Park, and Mr. Jung.

643
00:33:02,522 --> 00:33:03,482
It's been a while.

644
00:33:03,565 --> 00:33:06,318
All of you are even more glowing
since I last saw you.

645
00:33:10,739 --> 00:33:12,782
The young master just arrived
at the head office.

646
00:33:12,866 --> 00:33:14,367
Fishing is

647
00:33:14,451 --> 00:33:16,578
the art of waiting.

648
00:33:16,661 --> 00:33:18,663
When the time is right,

649
00:33:18,747 --> 00:33:20,332
they always bite.

650
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:24,461
What brings you here, Mr. Cha?

651
00:33:24,544 --> 00:33:26,880
I have received the occasional update.

652
00:33:26,963 --> 00:33:29,508
I hear you're running
some cosmetics startup nowadays,

653
00:33:29,591 --> 00:33:31,635
making some pocket change with that.

654
00:33:32,677 --> 00:33:35,889
But I hear you're having some real fun
buying up prime small and mid-caps

655
00:33:35,972 --> 00:33:37,599
and offloading them for a chunk of change.

656
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:40,769
Even in your Chail days, executives were
no more than spare parts to you.

657
00:33:40,852 --> 00:33:42,020
You haven't changed one bit.

658
00:33:42,103 --> 00:33:44,022
Well, since we're on the subject…

659
00:33:44,105 --> 00:33:46,608
That's the trend these days.

660
00:33:47,609 --> 00:33:49,194
Skills over bloodline.

661
00:33:49,277 --> 00:33:50,695
Isn't blind nepotism

662
00:33:50,779 --> 00:33:53,907
exactly the kind of outdated practice
the business world needs to shed?

663
00:33:53,990 --> 00:33:55,200
That's enough.

664
00:33:55,784 --> 00:33:58,578
You all know the Chairman

665
00:33:58,662 --> 00:34:02,040
has a soft spot for Se-gye,
in memory of the late Jin-u.

666
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:04,209
No formal appointment has been issued,

667
00:34:04,292 --> 00:34:06,294
yet our Se-gye came all this way.

668
00:34:06,795 --> 00:34:08,255
He must have a plan of some sort.

669
00:34:08,338 --> 00:34:09,381
Right,

670
00:34:09,464 --> 00:34:10,799
Se-gye?

671
00:34:14,803 --> 00:34:16,763
That's quite a long-winded welcome.

672
00:34:16,846 --> 00:34:18,265
So, in conclusion,

673
00:34:18,348 --> 00:34:21,393
I should know my place
and not go nosing around, right?

674
00:34:22,018 --> 00:34:24,437
What a shame.
This temper of mine is just nasty.

675
00:34:24,521 --> 00:34:26,439
Getting stepped on
only makes me more competitive.

676
00:34:26,523 --> 00:34:28,483
Mr. Choi Chi-won,
the new CEO of Chail Distribution.

677
00:34:28,567 --> 00:34:30,026
You say startups make pocket change,

678
00:34:30,110 --> 00:34:32,112
but maybe you should make some
before you speak.

679
00:34:32,195 --> 00:34:33,863
I saw sales this quarter

680
00:34:33,947 --> 00:34:35,907
dropped 31% from pre-appointment figures.

681
00:34:36,866 --> 00:34:38,827
But the stock price is steady!

682
00:34:38,910 --> 00:34:41,079
Next, we have
Park Sang-tae, CEO of Chail Bio.

683
00:34:41,162 --> 00:34:43,498
You said I treated you all
like spare parts.

684
00:34:43,582 --> 00:34:45,375
Did your <i>humanistic</i> management principles

685
00:34:45,458 --> 00:34:46,459
lead you to penalize

686
00:34:46,543 --> 00:34:48,628
every parental leave applicant
for negligence

687
00:34:48,712 --> 00:34:50,338
and push contract conversions?

688
00:34:50,422 --> 00:34:52,424
Next, we have the cousin
of the youngest sister

689
00:34:52,507 --> 00:34:54,676
of my older aunt's ex-husband.

690
00:34:54,759 --> 00:34:57,053
Mr. Jung Bon-gu,
the CEO of Chail Chemical.

691
00:34:57,137 --> 00:34:59,973
Before my aunt's divorce was finalized,
you shamelessly haunted

692
00:35:00,056 --> 00:35:01,891
Grandfather's doorstep to worm your way

693
00:35:01,975 --> 00:35:04,436
into a subsidiary role.
And now you call foul on nepotism?

694
00:35:04,519 --> 00:35:05,562
Such glaring hypocrisy

695
00:35:05,645 --> 00:35:07,480
from a great benefactor
of an arranged marriage.

696
00:35:07,564 --> 00:35:09,774
What? "Glaring hypocrisy"?

697
00:35:09,858 --> 00:35:10,900
Se-gye.

698
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:12,569
Stop there.

699
00:35:13,278 --> 00:35:15,655
Even as the Chairman's direct descendant,

700
00:35:15,739 --> 00:35:19,326
an outsider has no right to crash
a board meeting before being appointed.

701
00:35:19,409 --> 00:35:22,162
We're discussing important matters.
You should leave now.

702
00:35:24,623 --> 00:35:25,915
Is that so?

703
00:35:26,541 --> 00:35:27,959
In that case,

704
00:35:29,044 --> 00:35:30,920
shouldn't you leave first?

705
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:34,299
You're being shipped off
to the US branch tomorrow.

706
00:35:34,382 --> 00:35:35,425
You chairing this meeting

707
00:35:35,508 --> 00:35:37,510
doesn't really make much sense, does it?

708
00:35:39,471 --> 00:35:42,390
I'll show you all
on my first official day back at Chail.

709
00:35:43,099 --> 00:35:45,935
How I clawed my way up here,
crushing that "half-breed chaebol" label.

710
00:35:46,019 --> 00:35:48,146
I'll prove myself properly then.

711
00:36:00,450 --> 00:36:01,785
How amusing.

712
00:36:01,868 --> 00:36:04,537
After having all that fun out there
with your "self-made man" act,

713
00:36:04,621 --> 00:36:06,122
have you finally grown up?

714
00:36:06,956 --> 00:36:08,166
Then again…

715
00:36:10,585 --> 00:36:13,296
reality was never going to be
as rosy as you imagined.

716
00:36:13,380 --> 00:36:15,215
Drop the unbothered act already.

717
00:36:16,257 --> 00:36:17,801
You're clearly sweating bullets.

718
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:20,220
If anyone's actually unbothered here,
it’s you.

719
00:36:20,303 --> 00:36:23,348
I've never once had the luxury
of being relaxed.

720
00:36:23,431 --> 00:36:27,268
Unlike you, I wasn't born
with a diamond-encrusted silver spoon.

721
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:30,647
I had to work my ass off
just to reach the starting line.

722
00:36:31,272 --> 00:36:33,858
You make it sound like you are
a rags-to-riches success story.

723
00:36:33,942 --> 00:36:35,402
The spoon you were born with

724
00:36:35,485 --> 00:36:37,487
allowed you to stand before me now.

725
00:36:37,570 --> 00:36:39,239
Although that too comes to an end today.

726
00:36:40,073 --> 00:36:41,241
Do you

727
00:36:41,324 --> 00:36:43,326
honestly think
I'll just step down quietly?

728
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:49,374
You're the one who needs to wake up.

729
00:36:49,457 --> 00:36:51,334
My patience has its limits.

730
00:36:53,044 --> 00:36:54,921
Why else would I have put up with you?

731
00:36:55,004 --> 00:36:56,089
What?

732
00:36:56,172 --> 00:36:57,841
I let all your antics slide up until now

733
00:36:57,924 --> 00:37:00,135
because I still felt
some trace of gratitude.

734
00:37:00,218 --> 00:37:01,428
You saved Grandfather, after all.

735
00:37:01,511 --> 00:37:02,387
But,

736
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:04,556
that gratitude ends here.

737
00:37:04,639 --> 00:37:06,641
I'm done watching you mess with my people.

738
00:37:06,725 --> 00:37:09,561
So quit scheming from the shadows,
and face me head-on.

739
00:37:13,732 --> 00:37:14,899
You sure…

740
00:37:16,609 --> 00:37:17,652
you can handle that?

741
00:37:19,863 --> 00:37:21,489
Absolutely.

742
00:37:22,699 --> 00:37:25,034
Former President Choi Mun-do.

743
00:37:40,049 --> 00:37:41,301
- Seo-ri.
- Hey.

744
00:37:41,801 --> 00:37:43,553
Why'd you make me run over here?

745
00:37:43,636 --> 00:37:45,889
- Did something happen?
- Did you do something to the minx?

746
00:37:45,972 --> 00:37:48,516
No, I didn't do anything. Why do you ask?

747
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:49,476
Really?

748
00:37:50,059 --> 00:37:52,353
Then why is she telling me to fire you?

749
00:37:54,272 --> 00:37:55,398
Ji-hyo wants me fired?

750
00:37:55,482 --> 00:37:57,901
She was spouting nonsense
about not liking your face,

751
00:37:57,984 --> 00:37:59,611
so I told her to shut her trap.

752
00:37:59,694 --> 00:38:00,987
Keep a low profile for now.

753
00:38:01,070 --> 00:38:03,573
I still do not have
as much clout as that minx,

754
00:38:03,656 --> 00:38:06,618
- so keep your head down.
- Firing someone over that…

755
00:38:06,701 --> 00:38:08,244
Okay.

756
00:38:12,791 --> 00:38:13,666
What the…

757
00:38:14,542 --> 00:38:15,752
This is…

758
00:38:17,462 --> 00:38:18,588
But…

759
00:38:31,351 --> 00:38:32,602
You should've looked after it.

760
00:38:32,685 --> 00:38:34,354
The wardrobe team says there's no backup.

761
00:38:34,437 --> 00:38:36,439
Sir, someone did this
while she was in the restroom.

762
00:38:36,523 --> 00:38:37,816
Why are you blaming her?

763
00:38:37,899 --> 00:38:39,984
I'm just frustrated too.

764
00:38:40,068 --> 00:38:43,071
Damn it. This is going to mess up
the whole schedule.

765
00:38:43,154 --> 00:38:46,032
We'll shoot the bedroom scene first,

766
00:38:46,115 --> 00:38:47,075
so let's get ready.

767
00:38:47,158 --> 00:38:48,368
You get changed.

768
00:38:48,451 --> 00:38:50,453
You go get your hair done. Hurry up.

769
00:38:50,537 --> 00:38:51,704
Let's move it.

770
00:38:54,666 --> 00:38:57,252
Shin Seo-ri is really something else.

771
00:38:57,794 --> 00:39:00,004
She stirs up trouble wherever she goes.

772
00:39:00,088 --> 00:39:02,757
<i>- Did you hear the rumor?</i>
<i>- Is it time to get the funds ready?</i>

773
00:39:02,841 --> 00:39:06,135
<i>Biojei is finally out of the gutter</i>
<i>and headed to the moon!</i>

774
00:39:06,219 --> 00:39:08,304
It's like they have cameras following me.

775
00:39:09,055 --> 00:39:11,474
How did they even find out
I was here today?

776
00:39:12,100 --> 00:39:13,935
Sir, how did your first move land?

777
00:39:14,018 --> 00:39:15,979
Practically a brush with death.

778
00:39:16,062 --> 00:39:18,231
We have a long way to go.
Best we keep things smooth.

779
00:39:18,314 --> 00:39:19,357
Fine.

780
00:39:20,316 --> 00:39:22,861
That's enough for a warm-up.
Let's head back to the office.

781
00:39:22,944 --> 00:39:24,529
We should stop by Hannam-dong first.

782
00:39:24,612 --> 00:39:25,947
The Chairman summoned you.

783
00:39:27,657 --> 00:39:30,159
<i>Thank you for inviting us, Chairman.</i>

784
00:39:30,243 --> 00:39:33,872
I've heard you were
quite fond of my Tae-hee.

785
00:39:33,955 --> 00:39:36,624
I see Tae-hee grew up
to be so bright and smart,

786
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:38,585
all thanks to you.

787
00:39:38,668 --> 00:39:41,504
I'll be sure to keep that in mind
and take good care of her.

788
00:39:41,588 --> 00:39:43,631
I'll be sure to serve you well.

789
00:39:43,715 --> 00:39:46,301
She already sounds like
she's a part of this family.

790
00:39:52,557 --> 00:39:54,100
Se-gye, you're here.

791
00:39:57,270 --> 00:40:00,356
- I see we have guests.
- Yes, come sit down.

792
00:40:07,071 --> 00:40:09,240
Do you have a date in mind

793
00:40:09,324 --> 00:40:11,034
for the ceremony?

794
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:12,869
Tae-hee is still young.

795
00:40:12,952 --> 00:40:14,454
And she has career ambitions.

796
00:40:14,537 --> 00:40:16,372
I'd like to see them take it slow

797
00:40:16,456 --> 00:40:17,999
and let things progress naturally.

798
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:19,334
I respect your wishes.

799
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:22,003
Let's have them get engaged first.

800
00:40:22,086 --> 00:40:24,839
And there's no harm
in taking our time with the wedding.

801
00:40:25,548 --> 00:40:26,633
Right, Se-gye?

802
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:32,722
I hope you found
today's meal satisfactory.

803
00:40:32,805 --> 00:40:36,309
If I had known, I would've treated you
at a proper place, not at home.

804
00:40:36,392 --> 00:40:38,853
This is hardly the proper treatment
for a business partner.

805
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:39,812
What a shame.

806
00:40:44,525 --> 00:40:46,444
I should get back to the office now.

807
00:40:46,527 --> 00:40:47,862
Please excuse me.

808
00:40:47,946 --> 00:40:49,155
Sit down, Se-gye.

809
00:40:49,238 --> 00:40:51,282
If you need to tell me something else,

810
00:40:51,950 --> 00:40:52,992
I can come back later.

811
00:40:55,370 --> 00:40:56,371
Why, that…

812
00:40:57,914 --> 00:41:00,333
Goodness. Please forgive his discourtesy.

813
00:41:00,416 --> 00:41:02,502
I'll go see Se-gye out.

814
00:41:02,585 --> 00:41:03,878
Se-gye!

815
00:41:03,962 --> 00:41:05,296
You can't just leave like this.

816
00:41:05,380 --> 00:41:06,631
You'll upset my mom.

817
00:41:10,009 --> 00:41:12,053
Not coming would've been
the easiest solution.

818
00:41:12,136 --> 00:41:14,347
Is it because of that woman?

819
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:15,306
Must you be so rude?

820
00:41:16,349 --> 00:41:19,102
I thought you were smart,
but you have a terrible memory.

821
00:41:19,185 --> 00:41:20,979
I made my position clear last time.

822
00:41:21,062 --> 00:41:22,689
I said my office
will announce the breakup.

823
00:41:22,772 --> 00:41:25,566
Ever consider you might be the rude one
for blatantly ignoring that?

824
00:41:25,650 --> 00:41:27,902
You know you can't just end this
with one clean stroke.

825
00:41:27,986 --> 00:41:30,947
Mochang and Chail have already signed
a business agreement.

826
00:41:31,030 --> 00:41:32,782
There's a lot at stake here.

827
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:34,450
That's why I'm tolerating you.

828
00:41:35,326 --> 00:41:36,869
And your incessant rudeness.

829
00:41:38,371 --> 00:41:40,999
Keep my woman's name
out of your mouth from now on.

830
00:41:41,082 --> 00:41:44,460
I already feel like crap knowing
I'm causing her unnecessary grief.

831
00:41:52,427 --> 00:41:54,512
That's what happens
when you act out of character.

832
00:41:54,595 --> 00:41:56,889
And why did you make so much?

833
00:41:56,973 --> 00:41:58,766
It is fine. I will just eat it all.

834
00:41:58,850 --> 00:42:00,268
You can't eat all this by yourself.

835
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:02,061
Just leave it. I'll take care of it.

836
00:42:02,145 --> 00:42:03,229
And what can you do?

837
00:42:03,312 --> 00:42:06,691
I can just drop by school
and share it with my underclassmen.

838
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:09,152
Really? That is a great idea.

839
00:42:09,777 --> 00:42:11,738
Hurry up and go before it goes bad.

840
00:42:15,450 --> 00:42:17,869
- Where are you going?
- It is a secret.

841
00:42:17,952 --> 00:42:20,371
What secret? I thought we agreed
there'd be no secrets between us.

842
00:42:20,455 --> 00:42:22,832
Well, I made a little something,

843
00:42:22,915 --> 00:42:24,917
so I came to share it with my grandma.

844
00:42:25,001 --> 00:42:25,877
I see.

845
00:42:27,587 --> 00:42:28,713
Then should I come too?

846
00:42:29,464 --> 00:42:32,300
That is enough nonsense.
Hang up. I will call you later.

847
00:42:36,012 --> 00:42:37,180
Is it just my imagination?

848
00:42:37,263 --> 00:42:39,682
We're dating,
but the vibe hasn't changed at all.

849
00:42:41,642 --> 00:42:44,479
<i>It's not really about catching feelings.</i>
<i>I think she's genuinely worried.</i>

850
00:42:44,562 --> 00:42:45,646
More specifically…

851
00:42:46,898 --> 00:42:47,940
your stamina?

852
00:42:48,024 --> 00:42:49,942
<i>Yeah, I think she's worried about that.</i>

853
00:42:50,026 --> 00:42:50,985
As if.

854
00:42:52,695 --> 00:42:54,363
Have I gotten too soft lately?

855
00:42:56,365 --> 00:42:58,367
It's time to show her a real man.

856
00:42:59,786 --> 00:43:00,661
Mr. Son.

857
00:43:01,704 --> 00:43:03,414
- Wow.
- Gosh.

858
00:43:03,498 --> 00:43:05,458
You're amazing!

859
00:43:05,958 --> 00:43:07,877
I was actually craving something sweet.

860
00:43:07,960 --> 00:43:09,087
Thank you so much.

861
00:43:09,170 --> 00:43:10,671
Are these candied apples?

862
00:43:10,755 --> 00:43:13,466
It is nothing special,
but I appreciate the response.

863
00:43:14,884 --> 00:43:17,887
You might get thirsty, so go get
some iced Americanos too.

864
00:43:18,971 --> 00:43:19,972
- Here.
- No.

865
00:43:20,056 --> 00:43:21,390
That will land us in big trouble.

866
00:43:21,474 --> 00:43:24,227
Really? Then I shall go buy them myself.

867
00:43:24,310 --> 00:43:26,646
Hey, have you seen the patient in Room 12?

868
00:43:26,729 --> 00:43:27,939
I can't find her.

869
00:43:28,022 --> 00:43:30,358
Room 12 is Ms. Nam Ok-sun.

870
00:43:33,319 --> 00:43:36,906
<i>We'll check the CCTV first,</i>
<i>so please just wait here.</i>

871
00:43:51,712 --> 00:43:53,798
EXIT

872
00:43:56,843 --> 00:43:57,732
SONGJIN GENERAL HOSPITAL

873
00:44:17,530 --> 00:44:19,365
<i>Where on earth can she be?</i>

874
00:44:19,448 --> 00:44:21,200
<i>It will get dark soon.</i>

875
00:44:24,078 --> 00:44:25,621
Grandma!

876
00:44:25,705 --> 00:44:28,166
- Oh my.
- Where have you been?

877
00:44:29,417 --> 00:44:30,751
I just stepped outside

878
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:32,420
for a stroll.

879
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:34,672
You should have told someone
before you did.

880
00:44:34,755 --> 00:44:35,631
You scared me.

881
00:44:36,257 --> 00:44:38,384
Why would you be scared?

882
00:44:38,467 --> 00:44:40,428
Am I a child or something?

883
00:44:42,096 --> 00:44:44,182
From now on, tell someone
before you step out.

884
00:44:44,265 --> 00:44:46,225
And never go anywhere alone, okay?

885
00:44:46,309 --> 00:44:48,352
Jeez. Am I in prison?

886
00:44:49,061 --> 00:44:51,314
Can't even do what I want
with my own body.

887
00:44:52,481 --> 00:44:54,400
- What's that?
- What?

888
00:44:55,026 --> 00:44:56,194
It's nothing.

889
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:58,237
Nothing.

890
00:44:58,321 --> 00:45:00,489
Nothing at all.

891
00:45:01,073 --> 00:45:02,909
I told you it's nothing.

892
00:45:04,410 --> 00:45:05,286
CHAIL E&C

893
00:45:11,292 --> 00:45:13,294
LAND PURCHASE AGREEMENT

894
00:45:16,964 --> 00:45:18,841
SELLER: NAM OK-SUN
BUYER: CHAIL E&C

895
00:45:24,931 --> 00:45:26,474
CEO CHOI MUN-DO

896
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:28,184
Not just a stroll.

897
00:45:31,896 --> 00:45:34,941
She has been a bit more confused recently.

898
00:45:35,566 --> 00:45:37,735
Given her advanced age,

899
00:45:37,818 --> 00:45:40,488
it's unlikely her condition will improve.

900
00:45:51,332 --> 00:45:53,793
- Will you be paying in full?
- Of course.

901
00:45:54,752 --> 00:45:55,878
A real man pays in full.

902
00:45:55,962 --> 00:45:57,380
Pardon?

903
00:46:00,132 --> 00:46:02,385
You can use this account
for any future payments.

904
00:46:02,468 --> 00:46:03,970
That card has no limit.

905
00:46:04,053 --> 00:46:05,554
Unlimited. No limit.

906
00:46:06,347 --> 00:46:08,099
I see. Okay.

907
00:46:09,642 --> 00:46:11,978
Now that I handled the payment
like a real man,

908
00:46:12,061 --> 00:46:13,436
can you tell me Ms. Nam Ok-sun's

909
00:46:13,969 --> 00:46:14,855
room number?

910
00:46:14,939 --> 00:46:16,565
Goodness me.

911
00:46:32,581 --> 00:46:34,417
You're my Seo-ri's

912
00:46:35,376 --> 00:46:36,877
boyfriend?

913
00:46:36,961 --> 00:46:38,087
Yes, Grandmother.

914
00:46:39,130 --> 00:46:40,756
We are officially dating.

915
00:46:42,508 --> 00:46:46,429
Well, your face…

916
00:46:53,352 --> 00:46:54,353
looks good.

917
00:46:55,521 --> 00:46:56,605
A man's man.

918
00:46:57,231 --> 00:46:58,149
Right?

919
00:46:58,232 --> 00:47:00,651
I hear that I'm a man's man all the time.

920
00:47:03,362 --> 00:47:04,739
I'm telling the truth. Yes.

921
00:47:06,365 --> 00:47:09,076
Can I be shameless

922
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:11,412
and ask a favor of you?

923
00:47:11,495 --> 00:47:12,705
Yes, of course.

924
00:47:15,791 --> 00:47:17,710
When my Seo-ri was growing up…

925
00:47:20,421 --> 00:47:22,882
I never did anything

926
00:47:22,965 --> 00:47:24,467
properly for her.

927
00:47:26,802 --> 00:47:29,472
I was too busy running the restaurant.

928
00:47:34,977 --> 00:47:36,562
She practically raised herself.

929
00:47:38,064 --> 00:47:41,359
So when people called her mature,

930
00:47:42,276 --> 00:47:44,737
I was happy
because I thought it was a compliment.

931
00:47:47,239 --> 00:47:48,366
Like a fool.

932
00:47:49,033 --> 00:47:50,743
A child should act like a child.

933
00:47:51,452 --> 00:47:53,287
When a child acts mature,

934
00:47:53,788 --> 00:47:55,414
it means they're hurting inside.

935
00:47:56,165 --> 00:47:58,125
She only has the body of an adult.

936
00:47:58,667 --> 00:47:59,877
My Seo-ri still has

937
00:48:01,670 --> 00:48:02,922
a child's heart.

938
00:48:05,091 --> 00:48:07,510
She's a child who can't even look…

939
00:48:09,845 --> 00:48:11,013
into her own heart.

940
00:48:12,098 --> 00:48:13,974
I won't ask for anything else.

941
00:48:14,058 --> 00:48:15,643
Just don't leave her alone.

942
00:48:17,561 --> 00:48:19,730
Stay by her side so she doesn't keep it

943
00:48:20,564 --> 00:48:22,233
all bottled up inside.

944
00:48:24,235 --> 00:48:26,195
That's all I ask.

945
00:48:27,863 --> 00:48:28,989
Yes, Grandmother.

946
00:48:30,199 --> 00:48:31,492
I won't leave her alone.

947
00:48:33,494 --> 00:48:35,496
I'll never let her feel lonely.

948
00:48:38,582 --> 00:48:39,792
Then that's enough.

949
00:48:40,751 --> 00:48:42,670
That's all I need. Yes.

950
00:48:49,176 --> 00:48:50,970
Don't worry too much, Grandmother.

951
00:48:51,637 --> 00:48:53,806
I'm incredibly capable.

952
00:48:53,889 --> 00:48:56,058
I promise she'll never
have to lift a finger.

953
00:48:56,142 --> 00:48:58,352
This boy sure has a way with words.

954
00:48:59,687 --> 00:49:01,647
I do have a way with words.

955
00:49:01,730 --> 00:49:04,316
Some people even call me
a wordsmith warrior.

956
00:49:04,984 --> 00:49:07,236
I can't believe this.
I haven't even offered my guest

957
00:49:07,319 --> 00:49:09,196
a glass of water yet.

958
00:49:09,280 --> 00:49:10,322
Give me a second.

959
00:49:10,406 --> 00:49:11,407
Gosh.

960
00:49:23,544 --> 00:49:25,546
LAND PURCHASE AGREEMENT

961
00:49:27,673 --> 00:49:29,800
SELLER: NAM OK-SUN
BUYER: CHAIL E&C

962
00:49:36,432 --> 00:49:38,309
<i>She vanished all of a sudden earlier.</i>

963
00:49:38,392 --> 00:49:40,561
<i>Her granddaughter got quite a fright.</i>

964
00:49:40,644 --> 00:49:42,646
You sure you can handle that?

965
00:49:45,733 --> 00:49:47,485
This prick must be insane.

966
00:50:02,625 --> 00:50:05,085
I knew you were reckless,

967
00:50:05,169 --> 00:50:07,338
but I did not know
you were this shameless.

968
00:50:07,963 --> 00:50:10,216
Luring and threatening
a helpless old woman?

969
00:50:10,299 --> 00:50:12,009
And you still call yourself human?

970
00:50:13,928 --> 00:50:14,970
Gosh.

971
00:50:16,013 --> 00:50:17,097
Ms. Shin.

972
00:50:18,265 --> 00:50:19,683
I see you're very upset.

973
00:50:19,767 --> 00:50:21,894
But let's get the facts straight.

974
00:50:21,977 --> 00:50:24,772
There were no threats,
and we explained everything fully.

975
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:26,815
She signed it of her own free will.

976
00:50:27,358 --> 00:50:29,443
You took advantage of her confused state,

977
00:50:30,110 --> 00:50:31,820
and you claim it was not coercion?

978
00:50:36,033 --> 00:50:37,284
Just looking at your face

979
00:50:37,368 --> 00:50:39,119
makes me sick to my stomach.

980
00:50:39,203 --> 00:50:40,663
And now I know why.

981
00:50:40,746 --> 00:50:44,124
It is that forked tongue of yours
that leads people astray.

982
00:50:44,667 --> 00:50:46,001
The most vile abomination.

983
00:50:46,877 --> 00:50:49,630
I am sorry it has been so long
since my last visit.

984
00:50:50,381 --> 00:50:51,340
It is you.

985
00:50:52,132 --> 00:50:53,634
Dan-sim of the Kang clan?

986
00:50:55,010 --> 00:50:55,928
Your Highness.

987
00:50:56,011 --> 00:50:58,180
What brings you to my brother's quarters?

988
00:50:58,264 --> 00:51:01,267
No one has set foot here in a long time.

989
00:51:01,350 --> 00:51:02,268
Pardon?

990
00:51:02,351 --> 00:51:04,311
These quarters once belonged

991
00:51:04,395 --> 00:51:06,146
to my late older brother.

992
00:51:06,230 --> 00:51:07,439
When I was young,

993
00:51:08,649 --> 00:51:10,859
it was my favorite place.

994
00:51:14,071 --> 00:51:15,552
My younger brother enjoyed it as well.

995
00:51:16,574 --> 00:51:18,409
<i>These are my secret quarters.</i>

996
00:51:18,492 --> 00:51:20,369
What are you doing here?

997
00:51:20,995 --> 00:51:23,539
<i>My younger brother</i>
<i>took care of this place.</i>

998
00:51:23,622 --> 00:51:25,040
He must have missed his older brother.

999
00:51:25,124 --> 00:51:26,375
That is who he is.

1000
00:51:26,458 --> 00:51:27,960
YEONGHWI CHAMBER

1001
00:51:28,043 --> 00:51:30,713
Benevolent and tender by nature.

1002
00:51:31,422 --> 00:51:33,591
He walled himself off
from the world behind a half-mask,

1003
00:51:33,674 --> 00:51:35,593
but I knew. Beyond that wall,

1004
00:51:36,302 --> 00:51:38,012
he harbored dreams of greatness.

1005
00:51:38,887 --> 00:51:41,098
- Dreams?
- Yes, dreams.

1006
00:51:41,181 --> 00:51:43,100
Dreams that ran aground and sank.

1007
00:51:45,269 --> 00:51:47,271
I know you were close
to my brother, Hyeon.

1008
00:51:47,354 --> 00:51:49,273
So I am sure my presence
makes you uncomfortable.

1009
00:51:49,356 --> 00:51:52,026
But know that I did not hate him.

1010
00:51:52,776 --> 00:51:54,695
There can only be one sun in the sky.

1011
00:51:55,613 --> 00:51:57,364
This is merely the order of things

1012
00:51:57,448 --> 00:51:59,199
when you are born a royal.

1013
00:52:01,493 --> 00:52:04,330
I too have a dream like Hyeon.

1014
00:52:04,413 --> 00:52:06,165
I seek to be a sovereign

1015
00:52:07,750 --> 00:52:09,501
who serves his people with all he has.

1016
00:52:11,128 --> 00:52:12,379
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

1017
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:16,175
Will you also become
a subject of my nation?

1018
00:52:23,932 --> 00:52:24,808
<i>How foolish.</i>

1019
00:52:24,892 --> 00:52:27,519
To think I was deceived
by that loathsome face

1020
00:52:27,603 --> 00:52:29,772
and cowered in fear, even for a moment.

1021
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:33,567
Fear?

1022
00:52:33,651 --> 00:52:34,902
You were afraid, Ms. Shin?

1023
00:52:34,985 --> 00:52:36,195
I was for a time.

1024
00:52:36,695 --> 00:52:39,156
Would he come back someday
if I waited long enough?

1025
00:52:40,324 --> 00:52:42,910
Could we be reunited someday
if I just stayed alive?

1026
00:52:43,702 --> 00:52:45,829
I waited and hoped like a fool.

1027
00:52:47,206 --> 00:52:48,874
Without knowing I was being used.

1028
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,835
But not anymore.

1029
00:52:52,336 --> 00:52:53,962
I am done being manipulated

1030
00:52:54,046 --> 00:52:55,881
by your intimidation and sweet talk.

1031
00:52:59,510 --> 00:53:00,511
Well…

1032
00:53:01,178 --> 00:53:03,263
It doesn't matter.

1033
00:53:03,347 --> 00:53:05,891
We already secured a signature.

1034
00:53:05,974 --> 00:53:07,309
The restaurant will be torn down,

1035
00:53:07,393 --> 00:53:10,187
and all you need to do
is collect the hefty compensation.

1036
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:16,694
You have nothing to lose, Ms. Shin.

1037
00:53:17,986 --> 00:53:18,862
And

1038
00:53:19,571 --> 00:53:21,490
I hope it works out with Se-gye.

1039
00:53:21,573 --> 00:53:23,158
I'm genuinely rooting for you,

1040
00:53:23,242 --> 00:53:24,952
so don't take it the wrong way.

1041
00:53:25,661 --> 00:53:27,538
You two really look good together.

1042
00:53:37,131 --> 00:53:38,173
Cha Se-gye!

1043
00:53:39,466 --> 00:53:41,218
Choi Mun-do, you crazy bastard!

1044
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:43,095
The couple came separately.

1045
00:53:43,178 --> 00:53:44,430
Failed to coordinate?

1046
00:53:44,513 --> 00:53:46,473
Shut your mouth before I rip it open.

1047
00:53:55,149 --> 00:53:56,233
This piece of paper?

1048
00:53:56,775 --> 00:53:58,068
It means nothing.

1049
00:53:58,152 --> 00:53:59,903
It's most certainly not legally binding.

1050
00:53:59,987 --> 00:54:02,865
With abduction and entrapment charges,
you'll be rotting in a cell.

1051
00:54:02,948 --> 00:54:05,409
Stay out of my sight before I kill you.

1052
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:24,344
Why did you come here alone?

1053
00:54:24,428 --> 00:54:26,013
You should have told me first.

1054
00:54:26,096 --> 00:54:27,264
I lost my bearings.

1055
00:54:27,347 --> 00:54:29,600
You promised to cut all ties
with Choi Mun-do

1056
00:54:29,683 --> 00:54:31,810
and make sure I'd be the first to know
if anything came up.

1057
00:54:31,894 --> 00:54:33,604
I told you I had my reasons.

1058
00:54:34,563 --> 00:54:36,565
Do you think I wanted to see him?

1059
00:54:36,648 --> 00:54:38,025
Things were getting complicated--

1060
00:54:38,108 --> 00:54:40,194
I hate seeing you involved
with Choi Mun-do.

1061
00:54:40,277 --> 00:54:41,945
I hate it!

1062
00:54:46,950 --> 00:54:48,410
Just leave it to me.

1063
00:54:48,494 --> 00:54:50,579
I'll protect you no matter what.

1064
00:54:54,708 --> 00:54:56,168
Who do you think you are?

1065
00:54:57,085 --> 00:54:59,338
Who are you to push your way
into my life like this?

1066
00:54:59,421 --> 00:55:01,381
Do you already consider yourself
my husband?

1067
00:55:01,465 --> 00:55:03,425
Is that why you treat me like a fool?

1068
00:55:03,509 --> 00:55:05,135
You know that's not what I meant.

1069
00:55:05,219 --> 00:55:07,054
You are even worse than him.

1070
00:55:07,137 --> 00:55:08,639
Treating me like some witless damsel.

1071
00:55:08,722 --> 00:55:10,057
You are even more hurtful!

1072
00:55:14,645 --> 00:55:17,314
Do not follow me.
I cannot stand the sight of you.

1073
00:55:32,704 --> 00:55:34,873
<i>I won't ask for anything else.</i>

1074
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:37,835
<i>Just don't leave her alone.</i>

1075
00:55:58,230 --> 00:55:59,982
You came without any notice.

1076
00:56:05,988 --> 00:56:07,155
What is it?

1077
00:56:07,239 --> 00:56:09,908
I have something to tell you about Se-gye.

1078
00:56:24,715 --> 00:56:26,216
Good morning, sir.

1079
00:56:26,300 --> 00:56:27,593
Jesus!

1080
00:56:27,676 --> 00:56:29,261
Not exactly a good morning.

1081
00:56:29,344 --> 00:56:30,596
You look pale.

1082
00:56:31,138 --> 00:56:32,222
Did you have a nightmare?

1083
00:56:32,306 --> 00:56:33,599
Reality is a nightmare.

1084
00:56:34,224 --> 00:56:35,767
I'm the world's biggest idiot.

1085
00:56:35,851 --> 00:56:38,145
Why? What did you do this time?

1086
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:39,730
My big mouth is the problem.

1087
00:56:39,813 --> 00:56:43,191
Why did I say it like that?
The least I could've done was comfort her.

1088
00:56:43,775 --> 00:56:45,777
You damn idiot.

1089
00:56:45,861 --> 00:56:47,112
Maybe I can't control my anger?

1090
00:56:47,195 --> 00:56:49,948
Well, is that the only thing
you can't control?

1091
00:56:50,991 --> 00:56:53,452
I can't even control how much I miss her.

1092
00:56:53,535 --> 00:56:55,245
This is no way to live.

1093
00:56:58,790 --> 00:57:00,792
I'm suddenly craving caffeine.

1094
00:57:04,379 --> 00:57:06,715
<i>Love-struck bosses are exhausting.</i>

1095
00:57:08,050 --> 00:57:10,010
- What was that?
- Pardon? No. What?

1096
00:57:10,093 --> 00:57:11,511
What? Pardon? No.

1097
00:57:12,262 --> 00:57:14,932
Could you open the console box?

1098
00:57:15,015 --> 00:57:16,266
Please.

1099
00:57:18,268 --> 00:57:20,312
That should help alleviate your fatigue.

1100
00:57:23,523 --> 00:57:25,067
I bought it just for you.

1101
00:57:25,150 --> 00:57:26,401
This relieves fatigue?

1102
00:57:26,485 --> 00:57:28,362
It's pretty popular nowadays.

1103
00:57:33,492 --> 00:57:36,495
Gosh. I can suddenly feel
my blood pumping.

1104
00:57:37,454 --> 00:57:38,497
Wow.

1105
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:43,001
<i>So damn petty.</i>

1106
00:57:43,085 --> 00:57:46,672
For now, let's post security
at her grandmother's hospital.

1107
00:57:46,755 --> 00:57:49,299
If they spot anyone suspicious,
have them report to me immediately.

1108
00:57:49,383 --> 00:57:50,425
And get out.

1109
00:57:50,509 --> 00:57:51,468
Right now.

1110
00:57:54,054 --> 00:57:55,110
Right here?

1111
00:58:18,328 --> 00:58:20,998
I told him not to follow me,
and he actually listened.

1112
00:58:22,624 --> 00:58:24,001
Petty little wretch.

1113
00:58:27,587 --> 00:58:28,672
No, wait.

1114
00:58:30,424 --> 00:58:32,843
I said I did not want to see his face.

1115
00:58:32,926 --> 00:58:34,386
What choice did he have?

1116
00:58:35,721 --> 00:58:37,514
But at least send a message.

1117
00:58:37,597 --> 00:58:39,349
Is he trying to worry me to death?

1118
00:58:39,433 --> 00:58:40,976
Damn jerk.

1119
00:58:42,436 --> 00:58:44,271
<i>You are even worse than him.</i>

1120
00:58:44,354 --> 00:58:46,148
Treating me like some witless damsel.

1121
00:58:46,231 --> 00:58:47,566
You are even more hurtful!

1122
00:58:49,276 --> 00:58:51,319
You idiot.

1123
00:58:52,612 --> 00:58:54,740
Why take it out on an innocent person?

1124
00:58:56,033 --> 00:58:57,701
He did not do anything wrong.

1125
00:59:06,877 --> 00:59:08,670
I should eat something first.

1126
00:59:09,254 --> 00:59:11,256
I need to keep my strength up
to fight and win.

1127
00:59:11,339 --> 00:59:14,801
JANGSUGOL PORK BACKBONE STEW

1128
00:59:31,651 --> 00:59:34,821
My goodness. This place is going
to be shuttered soon enough.

1129
00:59:34,905 --> 00:59:37,240
How do you have no customers?

1130
00:59:37,324 --> 00:59:38,658
It's our break time.

1131
00:59:38,742 --> 00:59:40,160
I made an exception for a regular.

1132
00:59:40,243 --> 00:59:41,912
Do you want to be kicked out? Get out!

1133
00:59:41,995 --> 00:59:42,871
Oh my,

1134
00:59:42,954 --> 00:59:44,581
you still possess such vitality.

1135
00:59:44,664 --> 00:59:46,750
You could easily go for another ten years.

1136
00:59:46,833 --> 00:59:48,293
Rotten geezer.

1137
00:59:49,044 --> 00:59:49,920
Want a large?

1138
00:59:50,003 --> 00:59:52,255
I came alone.
What the hell do I need a large for?

1139
00:59:52,339 --> 00:59:53,548
There's your party.

1140
01:00:13,193 --> 01:00:14,194
Damn it.

1141
01:00:14,277 --> 01:00:16,154
Who drives like that in an alleyway?

1142
01:00:18,448 --> 01:00:19,783
Hey, Mr. Cha.

1143
01:00:20,867 --> 01:00:22,494
Are you here for Seo-ri?

1144
01:00:22,577 --> 01:00:24,162
She went out a while ago.

1145
01:00:24,663 --> 01:00:26,039
When exactly?

1146
01:00:34,089 --> 01:00:35,048
You know,

1147
01:00:35,715 --> 01:00:36,883
whenever I see Se-gye,

1148
01:00:36,967 --> 01:00:39,010
he just always manages to make me angry.

1149
01:00:39,094 --> 01:00:41,179
He's so stubborn. He never listens.

1150
01:00:41,263 --> 01:00:44,307
He always insists
on doing everything alone.

1151
01:00:45,267 --> 01:00:47,519
I was so determined
to get the upper hand over that kid

1152
01:00:47,602 --> 01:00:49,563
that I even raised my hand to him.

1153
01:00:51,481 --> 01:00:52,566
Looking back now,

1154
01:00:53,150 --> 01:00:55,485
it still weighs on my heart.

1155
01:00:56,153 --> 01:00:57,863
I should've just embraced him.

1156
01:00:58,530 --> 01:00:59,656
I only have regrets now.

1157
01:01:02,033 --> 01:01:03,493
Growing up without a mom

1158
01:01:04,411 --> 01:01:06,246
must've been so lonely.

1159
01:01:07,581 --> 01:01:09,541
Instead of comforting him,

1160
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:12,169
I just pushed him so hard.

1161
01:01:29,394 --> 01:01:31,521
<i>That's why I want Se-gye</i>

1162
01:01:31,605 --> 01:01:33,982
to start a family of his own

1163
01:01:34,065 --> 01:01:35,525
and never be lonely again.

1164
01:01:35,609 --> 01:01:37,402
That's all I ask.

1165
01:01:42,115 --> 01:01:43,450
If that is the case,

1166
01:01:44,868 --> 01:01:46,328
you do not need to worry.

1167
01:01:46,411 --> 01:01:48,288
I know exactly

1168
01:01:48,997 --> 01:01:50,165
how wretched loneliness feels.

1169
01:01:50,999 --> 01:01:52,834
I will make sure he is never lonely again.

1170
01:01:52,918 --> 01:01:54,878
No, I don't mean that.

1171
01:01:54,961 --> 01:01:56,838
I don't mean two lonely people

1172
01:01:56,922 --> 01:01:58,632
leaning on each other.

1173
01:01:58,715 --> 01:02:01,593
I don't want it to be two broken people

1174
01:02:01,676 --> 01:02:04,054
giving what love they have.

1175
01:02:04,137 --> 01:02:05,347
I want Se-gye

1176
01:02:05,430 --> 01:02:07,641
to end up with someone who has

1177
01:02:07,724 --> 01:02:09,768
plenty of love to spare.

1178
01:02:11,519 --> 01:02:13,438
It's not that I dislike you.

1179
01:02:14,231 --> 01:02:16,983
It's just an old man's greed.

1180
01:02:17,067 --> 01:02:18,610
I just want Se-gye

1181
01:02:19,444 --> 01:02:21,905
to be surrounded by a big, noisy family.

1182
01:02:21,988 --> 01:02:23,907
Loved by his mother-in-law

1183
01:02:23,990 --> 01:02:25,575
and encouraged by his father-in-law.

1184
01:02:25,659 --> 01:02:27,410
I want him to feel fully supported.

1185
01:02:29,996 --> 01:02:32,624
Is that too much to ask?

1186
01:02:43,093 --> 01:02:44,177
Seo-jun!

1187
01:02:45,720 --> 01:02:46,596
Dad!

1188
01:02:54,354 --> 01:02:55,939
I missed you so much.

1189
01:03:11,037 --> 01:03:11,902
CHA SE-GYE

1190
01:03:14,791 --> 01:03:17,043
You can answer it. It's fine.

1191
01:03:51,703 --> 01:03:57,584
PERSONAL FREIGHT

1192
01:03:57,667 --> 01:03:59,627
<i>The caller you are trying to reach…</i>

1193
01:04:27,030 --> 01:04:30,575
INCOMING CALL
CHA SE-GYE

1194
01:04:47,759 --> 01:04:49,177
<i>The caller you are trying</i>

1195
01:04:49,260 --> 01:04:51,304
<i>to reach is unavailable.</i>
<i>You will be transferred to voicemail</i>

1196
01:04:51,388 --> 01:04:52,847
<i>after the beep.</i>

1197
01:04:55,266 --> 01:04:57,852
<i>Shin Seo-ri, I was wrong.</i>

1198
01:04:57,936 --> 01:04:59,062
MISSED CALL
CHA SE-GYE

1199
01:04:59,145 --> 01:05:01,314
<i>It's all my fault.</i>
<i>Just pick up your phone.</i>

1200
01:05:01,815 --> 01:05:03,566
<i>I'll wait here until you come home.</i>

1201
01:05:06,945 --> 01:05:09,447
INCOMING CALL
CHA SE-GYE

1202
01:05:28,883 --> 01:05:32,303
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

1203
01:05:53,408 --> 01:05:56,327
NAMSAN DATE
VINTAGE CAMERA, NAMSAN PHOTO

1204
01:06:00,029 --> 01:06:00,957
<i>- Shin Seo-ri.</i>
<i>- Step back.</i>

1205
01:06:01,040 --> 01:06:02,750
- Step back.
- Get out of my way.

1206
01:06:02,834 --> 01:06:03,793
<i>Shin Seo-ri, wake up.</i>

1207
01:06:03,877 --> 01:06:04,919
Wake up, Shin Seo-ri!

1208
01:06:05,003 --> 01:06:07,005
- Please clear the way.
- Make way.

1209
01:06:07,672 --> 01:06:10,758
<i>Turns out Choi Mun-do is</i>
<i>one nasty piece of work.</i>

1210
01:06:10,842 --> 01:06:13,136
<i>First, a few words</i>
<i>from Chairman Choi Mun-do.</i>

1211
01:06:13,219 --> 01:06:16,347
<i>The backlash is mounting</i>
<i>after carcinogenic substances</i>

1212
01:06:16,431 --> 01:06:17,599
<i>were discovered in Dynaestie.</i>

1213
01:06:17,682 --> 01:06:19,184
<i>She was found dead this morning.</i>

1214
01:06:19,267 --> 01:06:22,312
- Is that a person?
- Some items belonging to you were…

1215
01:06:22,395 --> 01:06:24,939
Your Highness, are you awake?

1216
01:06:25,023 --> 01:06:27,066
<i>- Where am I…</i>
- Go fetch the physician!

1217
01:06:27,150 --> 01:06:29,319
<i>Have I truly returned?</i>

1218
01:06:31,905 --> 01:06:33,907
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
